main event: A large, white, oblong object was observed backing off toward the ocean and faded from sight on 5 November 1957.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 20 to 30 minutes,The object was described as being large and white but no exact dimensions were provided,Venus was noted to be present in the southwest sky during the sighting,The object was observed visually with the naked eye,Major Charles W. Finnegan believed the sighting could be an unidentified flying object.
witness description: Major Charles W. Finnegan, Senior Controller on Duty
